13/10/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu met with Christopher J. Hoh, director of the US State Department Office for South East Europe on Thursday (October 12th). They discussed the situation in the region and latest developments in the Kosovo status talks.They also discussed the need to strengthen the rule of law and co-operation among state institutions in Albania. Hoh urged all parties to agree on electoral reforms, stressing the importance of holding free and fair local elections in compliance with democratic standards. (Albanian News - 13/10/06; Albanian President website - 12/10/06)
